text.tspan: Number of countries with basic statistical institutions, World
Censuses collect snapshots of the population, civil registers major events of individuals (such as their birth), and
population registers current information of individuals (such as their address). Statistical agencies gather
numerical information on a variety of topics.
Data source: Thomas Brambor et al. (2019)
